      "turn": 1,
      "actor": "gsd-code-fixer",
      "content": "Apply fixes to ALL code review findings from the Phase 16 code review. The REVIEW.md is at:\n`.planning/phases/16-session-tracker-tool-intelligence-event-tracker-deprecation-/16-REVIEW.md`\n\n## CRITICAL Fixes (must fix)\n\n### CR-01: subagentType aggregation heuristic broken\n**File:** `src/tools/hivemind/session-context.ts` (lines 197-203 in the handleAggregate function)\n**Problem:** The subagentType aggregation checks `continuity.sessionID.startsWith(\"hm-/hf-/gsd-\")` but real session IDs start with `\"ses_\"`. This ALWAYS returns \"generic-session\" — zero useful data.\n**Fix:** Use `continuity.delegatedBy?.subagentType` from the continuity record if available. Fall back to parsing session ID conventions but recognize `\"ses_\"` prefix as a legitimate session type. Better approach: read the parent's delegation record or use `continuity.sessionID` pattern more intelligently. At minimum, classify \"ses_\" as \"opencode-session\" instead of \"generic-session\" and extract agent type from delegation records when available.\n\n### CR-02: Session-not-found wrapped in success() instead of error()\n**File:** `src/tools/hivemind/hivemind-session-view.ts` (~line 42 in buildUnifiedView)\n**Problem:** When session is null, the function returns data with `error` field INSIDE a `success()` envelope. This corrupts the CQRS response contract — client expects `error()` for failures.\n**Fix:** When `!session`, return `renderToolResult(error(\"Session not found: \" + sessionId))` instead of the current partial data payload.\n\n### CR-03: Path-traversal guard uses forward slash\n**File:** `src/features/session-tracker/persistence/atomic-write.ts` (line ~142)\n**Problem:** Path-traversal guard `startsWith(trackerRoot + \"/\")` uses forward slash — breaks on Windows. Check if this is actually in the codebase; if found, replace with `path.sep` or `path.resolve()` comparison.\n\n## WARNING Fixes\n\n### WR-01: Duplicate safeSessionId definition\n**Files:** `src/schema-kernel/session-tracker.schema.ts` and `src/schema-kernel/session-view.schema.ts`\n**Problem:** `safeSessionId` is defined in both files — silent divergence risk.\n**Fix:** Export from one location and import in the other. The canonical location is `session-tracker.schema.ts`. Update `session-view.schema.ts` to import it.\n\n### WR-02: timeRange type mismatch\n**File:** `src/tools/hivemind/session-tracker.ts`\n**Problem:** Tool args declare `timeRange` as string type but Zod schema expects object `{ after?: string, before?: string }`. Also `filterJson` and `removeEmpty` schema params exist but are dead code in the handler.\n**Fix:** Align the tool args type with Zod schema. Remove dead parameters if confirmed unused.\n\n### WR-03: Root session status hardcoded as \"active\"\n**File:** `src/tools/hivemind/session-tracker.ts` (handleFilterSessions or filter-sessions handler)\n**Problem:** Root session entries added by handleFilterSessions always get status \"active\" instead of reading from actual data.\n**Fix:** Read actual session status from continuity file or project-index.\n\n### WR-04: Orphaned schema SessionViewDelegationFilterSchema\n**File:** `src/schema-kernel/session-view.schema.ts`\n**Problem:** `SessionViewDelegationFilterSchema` is exported from session-view.schema.ts but doesn't belong there — it's for delegation-status, not session-view.\n**Fix:** Either remove it (if unused) or add a comment noting it's shared.\n\n## Process\n1. Read each file before editing\n2. Fix EACH finding with a separate commit\n3. Run `npm run typecheck` after each fix\n4. Run `npm test` after all fixes\n5. Update REVIEW.md with fix status per finding\n",
